    <field name="scopecontent_teim">This collection includes materials related to Al Silverman's work as an author as well as his work as editor of Sport Magazine, editor and publisher at Viking Press, and CEO and chairman of Book of the Month Club. Included in these files are draft copies of articles and books, research, interviews, magazine and newspaper clippings, correspondence with editors, and fan mail. The collected materials illustrate the stages of Silverman's writing process. </field>
    <field name="scopecontent_teim">Most materials are in original format. </field>
    <field name="scopecontent_teim">SERIES DESCRIPTIONS</field>
    <field name="scopecontent_teim">SERIES I: Author Files </field>
    <field name="scopecontent_teim">This series includes materials from several stages of Silverman's career including materials related to his work as an essayist and book author as well as his work as an editor of Sport Magazine and editor and publisher at Viking Press. Included are drafts, correspondence with editors, fan mail, interviews, research notes, contracts and audiocassettes. </field>
    <field name="scopecontent_teim">Subseries A: Paper Files</field>
    <field name="scopecontent_teim">Subseries B: Audio Recordings removed from Paper Files</field>
    <field name="scopecontent_teim">Subseries C: Recorded Interviews</field>
    <field name="scopecontent_teim">SERIES II: Book of the Month Club Files</field>
    <field name="scopecontent_teim">Subseries A: Paper Files</field>
    <field name="scopecontent_teim">Subseries B: Videocassettes</field>
    <field name="scopecontent_teim">This series includes materials from Silverman's tenure as CEO and chairman of Book of the Month Club. Included are correspondence, press clippings and videocassettes as well as files related to Book of the Month Club: Sixty Years of Books in American Life, edited by Silverman.</field>
    <field name="scopecontent_teim">SERIES III: It's Not Over 'Til It's Over</field>
    <field name="scopecontent_teim">Subseries A: Paper Files</field>
    <field name="scopecontent_teim">Subseries B: Books</field>
    <field name="scopecontent_teim">Subseries C: Media</field>
    <field name="scopecontent_teim">Subseries D: Digital Data Storage</field>
    <field name="scopecontent_teim">This series is a 2004 accretion to the Al Silverman papers. It includes research materials for, and drafts of It's Not Over 'Til It's Over, a sports history book written by Silverman, published  in 2002.</field>
    <field name="bioghist_teim">Al Silverman, a noted sports writer, is author of 10 books and numerous essays published in, among other publications, Playboy, Saga, and Sport Magazine. Among his publications is I am Third, written with Gale Sayers, which became the acclaimed movie, "Brian's Song." </field>
    <field name="bioghist_teim">In addition to his writing, Silverman also worked as an editor and publisher. He was editor of Sport Magazine from 1951 to 1963 and was CEO and chairman of Book of the Month Club from 1972 to 1988. Most recently, Silverman served as editor and publisher at Viking Press from 1989 to 1997.</field>
    <field name="acqinfo_teim">The Al Silverman papers were donated by Al Silverman in 1998. Accretions were added to the collection in 2004 and 2009.</field>
    <field name="phystech_teim">Audiovisual and born-digital materials have not been preserved and are not available to researchers.</field>
